Though, if it is feasible, I don't think it's terrible to take some time off. I was forced to because of money, but that time off (five years) gave me the time, brain development, and experience to figure out what I really wanted to do. When I went back to college (which is what brought me to MN), it was completely different than what I started out in when I went straight out of high school.

